## 📡 API Usage

### Option 1: Using Evans CLI (Recommended for gRPC)

Install Evans:
```bash
# macOS
brew install evans

# Linux
curl -L https://github.com/ktr0731/evans/releases/download/v0.15.1/evans_linux_amd64.tar.gz | tar -zx && mv evans /usr/local/bin/
```

#### Create User

First, make sure both services are running (see step 4 above). Then:

```bash
# Option A: Use Evans with proto files (from wallet-system root)
evans -p packages/proto/proto/user/v1/user.proto localhost:50051

# In the Evans REPL:
call CreateUser
# Enter: {"email": "alice@example.com", "name": "Alice Smith"}
```

Example response:
```json
{
  "id": "clvxyz123...",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "name": "Alice Smith",
  "created_at": 1704067200000
}
```

#### Create Wallet

```bash
# From wallet-system root
evans -p packages/proto/proto/wallet/v1/wallet.proto localhost:50052

# In the Evans REPL:
call CreateWallet
# Enter: {"user_id": "clvxyz123...", "initial_balance": 50000}
```

**Note**: Use `host:port` format (colon, not space) when connecting to the server.

